Even though Alpha Mom is New York-based, their writing contributors, product reviewers, and online visitors are from all over the United States. Alpha Mom was started because, as counter-intuitive as it may seem, motherhood is not a natural instinct for many (many) women. Rather, connectedness is a new mom’s first instinct. And, with non-judgmental support and advice from other moms and parenting professionals, they try to help women embrace motherhood with confidence. As with everything, they all still have lots of questions and believe that there are no easy answers in parenting. You’ll often find us engaged in conversations either seeking or providing advice, all while trying to raise happy and healthy children. At Alpha Mom they are tolerant of all styles of parenting as they can all learn from each other. They don’t believe there is a perfect mom style. In fact, they see humor in motherhood’s imperfections. So, join us to learn, support and laugh at the messy and magical experience of being a mom.

Description: Tutoring, writing, assignment helping, social media, course video selling and purchasing services provided.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Bayise is a tutoring, writing, academic support and social media services business. We have built multiple platforms that provides in-person and web-based tutoring as well as social media connecting services. Our tutoring platform is called Bayise Tutor and the social media platform is named Bayise Social. The platforms can be used together or as separate, standalone apps. Bayise Tutor makes it easier for tutors to conduct in-person and online classes and reach out to more students to enhance their earning potential. At the same time, the platform makes it easier for students to get access to tens of thousands of online tutors in their subjects. Students can find tutors for everything from homework support to subject comprehension in areas where they are struggling. Students can also find support in completing assignments. The Bayise Tutor platform has been in development since 2019. It was recently incorporated in March 2021. We have already signed on dozens of tutors within a short period of time and now looking to expand our services to customers. Once fully operational, we expect hundreds of thousands to millions of students to signup and benefit from the Bayise Tutor platform. Our platform aims to make education easier and non-disruptive for students that have been especially hurt by the ongoing pandemic and cancellation of their classes. Bayise Tutor will make it easier for students and parents to find the best tutors in their area to provide one-on-one and group classes. We are currently in the process of setting up offices that will be used as tutoring centers to accommodate thousands of students. Apart from the tutoring services, we are also building an online social media platform, Bayise Social, that is aimed specifically at students and young people.  Bayise Social will be a big social media platform that will offer advanced social media services such as posting, chatting, commenting, audio call, video call, live stream, group calls, advertising and much more.  The social media platform is available both on mobile apps and as a website. The revenue stream for the business will come as a percentage commission from tutor earnings. We are looking to become affiliated with local government,  education providers and  school districts to help them enhance their services. The social media platform will also generate revenue from advertisers who can pay to reach out to our users. Advertisers will be charged based on reach and the number of clicks.

Description: Direct Management Group represents musical artists.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Martin Kirkup, Bradford Cobb and Steven Jensen are partners at Direct Management Group, an internationally successful music management company, which offers artistic and business services to a very select roster of artists. The company was founded in April of 1985 by Jensen and Kirkup, combining Steven's experience with top-line artists at the ICM Agency with Martin's acumen in strategic career planning at A&M Records.  Direct Management Group enjoyed early success in handling British "new wave" artists Echo & The Bunnymen, and Orchestral Manoeuvres in the Dark (gaining their first worldwide hit single with "If You Leave" and a platinum album in 1986), as well as guiding Bryan Ferry on his first International Tour in 1988. The success of The B-52's quadruple-platinum album "Cosmic Thing" (with its hit singles "Love Shack" and "Roam") in 1989, established the company as a secure home for unique artists intent on forging their own path to success. In 1991, Direct signed the San Francisco band Counting Crows, and enjoyed a massively successful ten-year run in which they sold 25 million albums worldwide while establishing a rock-solid touring base. During the nineties, Direct continued to develop by working with artists such as David Byrne, Tracy Chapman, and the New Radicals. Bradford Cobb joined Direct in June of 1998, and broadened the range of the company by signing The Go-Go's, and then Katy Perry in 2004.
Industry Groups: Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio

Headquarters Regions: Greater Baltimore-Maryland Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: American Cyanamid Company was a U.S.-based diversified company with businesses in several fields. The company was a manufacturer of agricultural chemicals, cosmetics, perfumes, building products, plastics and pharmaceuticals. The company was listed as a top 100 manufacturing company by Fortune magazine in the 1970s.  Cyanamid was founded in 1907 and employed over 100,000 people around the world by 2000. The company maintained a monopoly over tetracycline, an antibiotic used against bacterial infections. A theft of the organism led to the loss of the monopoly as rival companies were able to produce generic versions of the formula, leading to huge losses to the company.  The company sold most of its businesses in the early 2000s and is now operated under the name Cytec.
